9. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Cathcart 2nd Lord Cathcart had at least 1 daughter with Margaret Douglas."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1460–1535":"1460–1535","1466–1507":"1466–1507","–Male":"Surnud","1535":"1535","1466":"1466","about 1466":"umbes 1466","1460":"1460","1507":"1507","Cathcart, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Cathcart, Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1460–1535":"1460–1535","1466–1507":"1466–1507","–Male":"Kuollut","1535":"1535","1466":"1466","about 1466":"noin 1466","1460":"1460","1507":"1507","Cathcart, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Cathcart, Renfrewshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","1460–1535":"1460–1535","1466–1507":"1466–1507","–Male":"Décédé","1535":"1535","1466":"1466","about 1466":"environ 1466","1460":"1460","1507":"1507","Cathcart, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Cathcart, Renfrewshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"John Cathcart 2nd Lord Cathcart a eu au moins 1 fille avec Margaret Douglas."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1460–1535":"1460–1535","1466–1507":"1466–1507","–Male":"Verstorben","1535":"1535","1466":"1466","about 1466":"um 1466","1460":"1460","1507":"1507","Cathcart, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Cathcart, Renfrewshire, Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"John Cathcart 2nd Lord Cathcart hatte mit Margaret Douglas mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1460–1535":"1460–1535","1466–1507":"1466–1507","–Male":"Desede","1535":"1535","1466":"1466","about 1466":"about 1466","1460":"1460","